
# <type>(<optional scope>)<!>: <description>     ^
#   │           │          └─ Breaking changes must be indicated by a `!` immediately before the `:`
#   │           └─ Noun describing a section of the codebase
#   └─ fix|feat|build|chore|ci|docs|style|refactor|perf|test
#
# The body of the gitmessage should explain what and why (but not how).
# Use GFM for formatting and links (links should not be line-wrapped)
#
# Include footers where necessary:
# BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
# Co-authored-by: First Last <first.last@example.com>
# Reviewed-by: First Last
#
# The entirety of the gitmessage should wrap at 72 characters.         ^
